Year = {2025},
Month = {2025 AUG 18},
Abstract = {The introduction of Generative Artificial Intelligence (GenAI) into
   education represents a paradigm shift, offering both opportunities and
   challenges for educators. This qualitative study examines the
   perspectives of higher education (HE) educators on the use of GenAI
   tools like ChatGPT, Midjourney, and GitHub Copilot, focusing on their
   influence on learning outcomes, pedagogies, and assessment. The criteria
   for choosing participants-47 educators from different universities-were
   based on the participants' use of Gen AI in teaching their courses and
   their willingness to share their experiences on the use of AI GenThe
   research employs deductive and inductive thematic analysis to identify
   and analyze themes related to the integration of GenAI in education.
   Findings reveal that educators perceive GenAI as a potential tool for
   enhancing personalized learning experiences, content creation, student
   engagement, and innovative teaching methods. However, challenges such as
   ethical considerations, the need for training, the quality of generated
   content, academic integrity, and policy regulation are highlighted as
   significant concerns that need to be addressed to harness the full
   potential of GenAI in education effectively.},
